ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I have had the sensation after getting dressed that parts of my clothes (tags, collars, pant legs, etc.) didnt feel just right.
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: When placing a book back onto a shelf, I have had the sensation that it did not look just right with the other books.
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: When locking the door to my house, I have had the sensation that the feel of the lock locking wasnt just right.
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: I have had the sensation while folding my clothes that they did not look the way folded clothes should look.
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: I have had the sensation while writing something down that the words did not look just how I wanted them to look.
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: When talking to people, I have had the sensation that my words did not sound just right.
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: I have had the sensation while organizing my desk that my papers and other things didnt look just right.
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: When putting a bill or letter into a mailbox, I have had the sensation that the way I placed the envelope in the mailbox and closed the door didnt feel just right.
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: After washing my hands once, I have had the sensation that they did not feel just the way clean hands are supposed to feel.
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: When hanging a picture on the wall, I have had the sensation that it did not look just right.
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: The NJRE from the list above that occurred most recently is the following:
Notes: 1 = I have had the sensation after getting dressed that parts of my clothes (tags, collars, pant legs, etc.) did not feel just right; 2 = When placing a book back onto a shelf, I have had the sensation that it did not look just right with the other books; 3 = When locking the door to my house, I have had the sensation that the feel of the lock locking was not just right; 4 = I have had the sensation while folding my clothes that they did not look the way folded clothes should look; 5 = I have had the sensation while writing something down that the words did not look just how I wanted them to look; 6 = When talking to people, I have had the sensation that my words did not sound just right; 7 = I have had the sensation while organizing my desk that my papers and other things did not look just right; 8 = When putting a bill or letter into a mailbox, I have had the sensation that the way I placed the envelope in the mailbox and closed the door did not feel just right; 9 = After washing my hands once, I have had the sensation that they did not feel just the way clean hands are supposed to feel; 10 = When hanging a picture on the wall, I have had the sensation that it did not look just right

ElementDescription: The last time that the recent NJRE occurred was
Notes: 1= Within the past few hours; 2= Within the past day; 3= Within the past week; 4= Within the past month

ElementDescription: How frequently did you experience this NJRE?
Notes: 1= Never; 3= Within the past year; 5= Within the past month; 7= Within the past day

ElementDescription: How intense was this NJRE?
Notes: 1= Not intense at all; 4= Moderate intense; 7= Extremely intense

ElementDescription: To what degree did this NJRE bother you or cause you distress AT THE TIME?
Notes: 1= No distress at all; 4= Moderate distress; 7= Extreme distress

ElementDescription: To what degree did this NJRE bother you or cause you distress LATER THAT SAME DAY?
Notes: 1= No distress at all; 4= Moderate distress; 7= Extreme distress

ElementDescription: To what extent did you feel that you couldn't get this NJRE out of your mind?
Notes: 1= Not difficult at all to get it out of my mind; 4= Moderately difficult to get it out of my mind; 7= Extremely difficult to get it out of my mind

ElementDescription: To what extent did you have an urge to do something about this NJRE?
Notes: 1= No urge to do something; 4= Moderate urge to do something; 7= Extreme urge to do something

ElementDescription: To what extent did you feel that it was your responsibility to do something about this NJRE?
Notes: 1= Not at all responsible; 4= Moderately responsible; 7= Extremely responsible

ElementDescription: Frequency score
Intensity score
Immediate Distress score
Delayed Distress score
Rumination score
Urge to Respond score
Felt sense of responsibility score
Total number of NJRE
